to the editor former senator john c danforth op ed may 6 warns that overzealous prosecution of arthur andersen to restore confidence in american business could backfire a balanced approach is no doubt indicated but this should apply to both prosecution and prevention of corporate fraud president ronald reagan succeeded in convincing many that government regulation stifled free enterprise now underregulation seems to have brought us enron and other demoralizing business scandals we may not need more but we certainly need better federal regulation ex post facto prosecution wo n't prevent major fraud nor its effects on the economy and consumer confidence nicholas cunningham new york may 6 2003

